Class JFXDrawerEvent

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.EventObject
      • javafx.event.Event
        • com.jfoenix.controls.events.JFXDrawerEvent
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable

    public class JFXDrawerEvent
extends javafx.event.Event
    JFXDrawer events, used exclusively by the following methods:
    • JFXDrawer.open()
    • JFXDrawer.close()
    Since:
    2016-03-09
    See Also:
    Serialized Form

    • Field Summary

      Fields 
      Modifier and Type Field and Description
      static javafx.event.EventType<JFXDrawerEvent> CLOSED
      This event occurs when a JFXDrawer is closed, no longer visible to the user ( after the exit animation ends )
      static javafx.event.EventType<JFXDrawerEvent> CLOSING
      This event occurs when a JFXDrawer is being closed, will become invisible to the user at the end of the animation ( after the entrance animation ends )
      static javafx.event.EventType<JFXDrawerEvent> OPENED
      This event occurs when a JFXDrawer is drawn, visible to the user ( after the entrance animation ends )
      static javafx.event.EventType<JFXDrawerEvent> OPENING
      This event occurs when a JFXDrawer is being drawn, visible to the user ( after the entrance animation ends )
